  "text": "To gain further insights into the structural diversity of the potato metacaspase genes and to determine genetic relatedness in terms of length and number of introns/exons with certain other plant metacaspases, SotubMCs gene structures were analyzed. The study revealed a striking similarity in the number and length of exon/intron between potato and tomato metacaspases [CITATION_1] . Both the plant species exhibited the presence of six type I metacaspases with five exons separated by four introns, and also lengths of introns/exons of these metacaspases were highly similar except the length of SotubMC3 and SotubMC6, which were showing noticeable difference in first and last introns, respectively, with their corresponding counterparts SlMC3",
